## Clean Code Principles

This project follows the Clean Code standard in
[.claude/standards/CLEAN_CODE.md](.claude/standards/CLEAN_CODE.md). Read it in full;
the hard limits are:

| Rule | Limit |
|------|-------|
| **File length** | ~250 lines — split if approaching |
| **Function size** | 2-4 lines ideal, rarely >20 lines |
| **Max indent depth** | 1-2 levels |
| **Function arguments** | 0-2 ideal, never 3+ |
| **Flag (boolean) arguments** | Never — split into two functions |

Core rules: one level of abstraction per function, the step-down rule, Command-Query
Separation, no side effects, one word per concept, DRY, delete unused code completely.

**Code without tests is not clean.** Write a failing test first, then the minimal fix.

## Harness

This project uses the clean-code harness (agents, commands, standards) installed under
`.claude/`. These files are local-only (excluded from git via `.git/info/exclude`) and
are not pushed to the project's remote.

- `/clean <target>` — refactor code to the Clean Code standard
- `/commit` — conventional commit with verification
- `/fix-bug <desc>` — test-first bug fix (RED → GREEN → REFACTOR)
- `/create-plan` — milestone-based plan scaffold
- `/redesign <page>` — generate 5 distinct UI design explorations
- Agents: `clean-code-reviewer`, `test-writer`
